ntly the situation does not seem to be resolved.<\/p>\n","answer_id":2587,"question_id":2583,"up_vote_count":5}],"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/questions/2583/homologies-to-insect-wings","last_activity_date":1339444404,"creation_date":1339429019,"answer_count":1,"title":"Homologies to insect wings","body":"<p>All winged vertebrates have wings which are homologous to each other and to the forelimbs of the non-winged vertebrates. But what about insect wings? Are all insect wings homologous, and are there any homologies between insect wings and any vertebrate limbs?<\/p>\n","question_id":2583,"tags":["evolution","zoology","entomology","homology"],"score":6,"accepted_answer_id":2587,"down_vote_count":0,"is_answered":true,"view_count":238,"up_vote_count":6,"last_edit_date":1339444404},{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/1cdb5a1914de671ee56a7ea1483cb55c?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG","user_type":"unregistered","user_id":994,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/994/user132314","reputation":16,"display_name":"user132314"},"closed_date":1339438561,"comments":[{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/8729233d525a654914051bf8c1234c78?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG","user_type":"registered","user_id":115,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/115/nico","reputation":6011,"display_name":"nico","accept_rate":100},"score":0,"post_id":2584,"edited":false,"creation_date":1339434488,"comment_id":3602,"body":"There are thousands of different proteins in our body, some will make a wound heal, some will not make a difference, some could make the situation even worse, you cannot generalise."},{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/1cdb5a1914de671ee56a7ea1483cb55c?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG","user_type":"unregistered","user_id":994,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/994/user132314","reputation":16,"display_name":"user132314"},"score":0,"post_id":2584,"reply_to_user":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/