y structure to be characterized by non-covalent interactions such as hydrogen bonding, van der Waals interactions and whatnot. However, if two distinct polypeptides were <em>only<\/em> connected by one covalent disulfide bridge, would this be considered as quaternary structure, assuming that non-covalent interactions between the subunits are either negligible or even repulsive?<\/p>\n\n<p>In other words, <strong>can a disulfide bridge, on its own, convey quaternary structure?<\/strong>  <\/p>\n\n<p>On a side note, are there any notable examples of this type of interaction?<\/p>\n","question_id":2555,"tags":["proteins","structural-biology","protein-binding"],"score":3,"accepted_answer_id":2557,"down_vote_count":0,"is_answered":true,"view_count":395,"up_vote_count":3,"last_edit_date":1339189584},{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/3ba1f55d456c3a4213cfe9e44a748653?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG","user_type":"registered","user_id":602,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/602/anil","reputation":230,"display_name":"Anil"},"comments":[{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/ef10e56567f5d6e20bc3f7f4ab4e3254?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG","user_type":"registered","user_id":87,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/87/gaurav","reputation":683,"display_name":"Gaurav"},"score":1,"post_id":1350,"edited":false,"creation_date":1331284621,"comment_id":1648,"body":"Out of curiosity, what name are you looking for?"},{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/52bddd6ae812be4933dc7d26c41d96af?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG","user_type":"registered","user_id":154,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/154/abe","reputation":446,"display_name":"Abe","accept_rate":67},"score":0,"post_id":1350,"edited":false,"creation_date":1331309610,"comment_id":1653,"body":"I would go with results from the first site you mention (www.theplantlist.org)"},{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/ef067cf09ffd3cc8f069bacec73c8202?